"title": "7142: people of God, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7142",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The NT relates how the Christian church is the new people of God, assuming all the privileges and responsibilities of Israel in the OT, but with a universal mission to all the world, rather than any one nation.</p>\n<h2>NT believers are God's people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:22-Rom9:26\">ROM 9:22–9:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:10\">1PE 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:12\">2CO 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:3\">EPH 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:21\">REV 22:21</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are the true children of Abraham</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:9\">MAT 3:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8\">LUK 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16-Rom4:18\">ROM 4:16–4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:9\">GAL 3:6–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:22-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:22–4:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>The church is the people of God</h2>\n<h3>God's chosen people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:4\">1TH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>God's children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:6\">GAL 4:4–4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5\">EPH 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:14-Phil2:15\">PHP 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>God's possession</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></p>\n<h3>God's servants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:16\">1PE 2:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:1\">REV 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:20\">REV 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>The temple of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:19–2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:6\">HEB 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>The body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22-Eph1:23\">EPH 1:22–1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:5\">ROM 12:4–12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:13\">EPH 4:11–4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ sends believers into all the world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:10\">MRK 13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">LUK 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:20-John17:24\">JHN 17:20–17:24</a></p>",
